modularisation

Class ModuleExtractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • modularisation.ModuleExtractor

  • public class ModuleExtractor
extends java.lang.Object
    The CreateModule class contains methods for extracting modules from ontologies. A module is considered a logical subset of the ontology. This code is based on the OWL API functionality for extracting locality-based modules.
    Author:
    audunvennesland

      • modularise

        public static void modularise(java.lang.String monoFileName,
                              java.lang.String moduleName,
                              java.lang.String storageFolder,
                              java.lang.String seedSignature)
                       throws org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntologyStorageException,
                              org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntologyCreationException
        Extracts a module from an OWL ontology given a "seed signature".
        Parameters:
        monoFileName - The OWL ontology from which a module will be extracted.
        moduleName - The name given to the module extracted.
        storageFolder - The folder in which the extracted module will be placed.
        seedSignature - The signature guiding the extraction of the module. A seed signature can be an OWL entity (class, object property, etc.).
        Throws:
        org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntologyStorageException
        org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntologyCreationException
